Tips for Effective Support Reporting

Add the Parent Case Number field to reports when tracking cases. This indicates if a case is associated with a parent case.
Add the Closed When Created field to reports when tracking first-call resolution of cases. This indicates cases that were closed by support reps via the Save & Close button during creation.
Create custom report types for:
  - Translated Solutions: Summarize translated solutions associated with each master solution
  - Contact Role: Show all cases with their associated contact roles
  - Cases with Articles: See the articles attached to cases. This report is only available if Salesforce Knowledge is enabled.
  - Cases with Milestones: View a list of cases with milestones by choosing this report type if entitlements are enabled
  - Case History and Solution History: Track the history of standard and custom fields on cases and solutions where field histories are set up for tracking

Cases in Portals

Run reports to track usage of your Self-Service portal.
When reporting on case comments, use the Public Case Commented field to indicate if the comment is private or public.

Solution Categories

Create a custom report that sorts solutions by category. Select the Category Name and Parent Category Name fields to display solution categories and subcategories.

Team Members

Report on case teams in which you are a member.
Limit any case report to cases owned by users or cases in queues.
Choose User Owned Cases or Queue Owned Cases from the View drop-down at the top of a case report.
title: Effective Support Reporting with Salesforce Service Cloud
